  "text": "Remark 8.2. The assumption P 2 (S) ≥ 4 is necessary. Indeed if we consider a surface S with p g = q = 1, K 2 = g = 2 ( these surfaces are studied in [CITATION_1] ), then we have P 2 (S) = 3, and the bicanonical map is a covering of degree 8 of P 2 .",
